    <refsection id="Description_MMR_IdealPlanetary">
        <title>Description</title>
        <para>
            This block models is used for modeling an ideal planetary gear. The formula used to compute angular velocities is the
            Willis formula:
        </para>
        <para>
            <latex>
                \begin{eqnarray}
                \frac{\Large{\omega_{1/0}\:-\:\omega_{4/0}}}{\Large{\omega_{3/0}\:-\:\omega_{4/0}}} = \frac{\Large{Z_3}}{\Large{Z_1}} = ratio
                \end{eqnarray}
            </latex>
        </para>
        <para>
            with:
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <latex>\omega_{1/0}\:</latex> the angular velocity of the sun.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <latex>\omega_{3/0}\:</latex> the angular velocity of the ring.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <latex>\omega_{4/0}\:</latex> the angular vocity of the carrier.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <latex>Z_1\:</latex> the number of teeth of the sun.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <latex>Z_3\:</latex> the number of teeth of the ring.
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </para>
    </refsection>
